is, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/190783-astronants/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022190783\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/190783-astronants/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Astronants\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FellipeC","CreatedById":77983,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T12:14:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat the ABS Rate slider do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T12:40:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223698753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572691237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160709\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DfA-DoM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/2/2019 at 6:40 AM, DfA-DoM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease, follow \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E suggestion and include an equivalent of DoubleTapBrakes into your mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo need, just install both\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astronants","CreatedById":190783,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T13:26:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223698753\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572691237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160709\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DfA-DoM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/2/2019 at 11:40 AM, DfA-DoM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease, follow \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E suggestion and include an equivalent of DoubleTapBrakes into your mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently you can lock the brakes with alt\u002Bb. But I\u0027m not against the idea of switching from alt\u002Bb to double tap if people are interested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572783254\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277983\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FellipeC\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, FellipeC said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat the ABS Rate slider do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ABS rate slider allows you to change the time between two cycles of the anti-lock system (one cycle = one deactivation and reactivation of the brakes). It goes from 0.1s to 1s, quicker rate means safer landing but longer distance to stop, lower rate means shorter distance but can cause you craft to drift on the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FellipeC","CreatedById":77983,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T13:29:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572787598\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190783\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Astronants\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Astronants said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently you can lock the brakes with alt\u002Bb. But I\u0027m not against the idea of switching from alt\u002Bb to double tap if people are interested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ABS rate slider allows you to change the time between two cycles of the anti-lock system (one cycle = one deactivation and reactivation of the brakes). It goes from 0.1s to 1s, quicker rate means safer landing but longer distance to stop, lower rate means shorter distance but can cause you craft to drift on the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. I thought the exactly opposite, bigger numbers, brake quicker. Now it makes sense!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jognt","CreatedById":176871,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T14:38:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572787598\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190783\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Astronants\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Astronants said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently you can lock the brakes with alt\u002Bb. But I\u0027m not against the idea of switching from alt\u002Bb to double tap if people are interested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ABS rate slider allows you to change the time between two cycles of the anti-lock system (one cycle = one deactivation and reactivation of the brakes). It goes from 0.1s to 1s, quicker rate means safer landing but longer distance to stop, lower rate means shorter distance but can cause you craft to drift on the runway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recommend changing \u201CABS rate\u201D to \u201CABS interval\u201D as it should be a bit more intuitive in its meaning.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DfA-DoM","CreatedById":160709,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T16:51:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572784808\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo need, just install both\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1 mod for 1 line of code: isn\u0027t it a bit... overkill?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572787598\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190783\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Astronants\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Astronants said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently you can lock the brakes with alt\u002Bb. But I\u0027m not against the idea of switching from alt\u002Bb to double tap if people are interested.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be really nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not against having several mod acting together (currently playing with approx 50 active mods), but I think that the wheel brakes handling don\u0027t deserve many mods, possibly conflicting each other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-03T21:00:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572799872\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160709\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DfA-DoM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, DfA-DoM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1 mod for 1 line of code: isn\u0027t it a bit... overkill?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor a game that entirely about overkill? Moar mods! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astronants","CreatedById":190783,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-05T14:09:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699389\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572791907\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176871\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jognt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/3/2019 at 3:38 PM, Jognt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recommend changing \u201CABS rate\u201D to \u201CABS interval\u201D as it should be a bit more intuitive in its meaning.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat sounds interesting, I\u0027ll do it for the next update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astronants","CreatedById":190783,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-05T14:31:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223699440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221572799872\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160709\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DfA-DoM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/3/2019 at 5:51 PM, DfA-DoM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be really nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not against having several mod acting together (currently playing with approx 50 active mods), but I think that the wheel brakes handling don\u0027t deserve many mods, possibly conflicting each other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI opened an issue on Github including a link to a poll in which you guys can vote for how you want to toggle the brakes: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Astronants/SafeBrakes/issues/2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Astronants/SafeBrakes/issues/2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll also include a link to the poll in the next update. If it doesn\u0027t get enough votes btw I\u0027ll leave things as they are.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-11-05T14:34:39Z\u0022 title=\u002211/05/2019 02:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 5, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Astronants\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-06T20:46:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition to picking a method of toggling brakes on/off (rather than tap \u0026amp; hold or click the icon as in vanilla), would it be doable to include an option to enable/disable the ABS feature as well? For those moments when you just *want* to lock the brakes, and don\u0027t want to click on a pod and find the correct switch in time. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EOr, if it\u0027s exposable to an action group to toggle ABS on/off, that would work too.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI\u0027m voting mod-key, since double tapping can be finicky with response time, though I do use and love \u0027double tap brakes\u0027\u00A0as well.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MaxwellsDemon","CreatedById":147660,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-30T23:50:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCrossposting one of my posts from another thread:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m far from an expert in reading logs, but I\u0027m seeing a lot of these in the log when I was looking at said rover:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[ERR 17:36:00.062] Module SafeBrakes threw during OnUpdate: System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 at SafeBrakes.SafeBrakes.OnUpdate () [0x001b4] in \u0026lt;e8f4061f37b542f9b11eea8271dcef40\u0026gt;:0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 at Part.ModulesOnUpdate () [0x0004a] in \u0026lt;9d71e4043e394d78a6cf9193ad011698\u0026gt;:0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astronants","CreatedById":190783,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-02T13:43:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223711863\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575157824\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147660\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MaxwellsDemon\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/1/2019 at 12:50 AM, MaxwellsDemon said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCrossposting one of my posts from another thread:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m far from an expert in reading logs, but I\u0027m seeing a lot of these in the log when I was looking at said rover:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[ERR 17:36:00.062] Module SafeBrakes threw during OnUpdate: System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 at SafeBrakes.SafeBrakes.OnUpdate () [0x001b4] in \u0026lt;e8f4061f37b542f9b11eea8271dcef40\u0026gt;:0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0 at Part.ModulesOnUpdate () [0x0004a] in \u0026lt;9d71e4043e394d78a6cf9193ad011698\u0026gt;:0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, thanks for reporting the issue, I\u0027ll take a look at it and make an update asap. I\u0027ll also take a look at your original thread, some context could help me a lot in recreating and fixing it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astronants","CreatedById":190783,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-19T15:04:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENew SafeBrakes Update (1.1.5), NullRefs on update should be fixed.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChangelog\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n- poll results: toggle the brakes with modkey \u002B brakes [63%]\u003Cbr\u003E\n- updated InstallCheck and ModuleManager\u003Cbr\u003E\n- various bug fixes and improvements\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EDownload it on \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Astronants/SafeBrakes/releases/tag/1.1.5\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGithub\u003C/a\u003E or \u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/2127/SafeBrakes\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESpacedock\u003C/a\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-21T18:50:31Z\u0022 title=\u002212/21/2019 06:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 21, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Astronants\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dlrk","CreatedById":60033,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-01T17:03:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is amazing. Thank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dlrk","CreatedById":60033,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T04:32:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to just default this to on, instead of activating manually? Also, it would be awesome to have the brakes automatically activate on touchdown\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-11T05:13:44Z\u0022 title=\u002203/11/2020 05:13  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by dlrk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T14:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583901177\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dlrk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, dlrk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to just default this to on, instead of activating manually? Also, it would be awesome to have the brakes automatically activate on touchdown\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022143330\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1149177755\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/150666-19x-auto-actions-continued-v1111-%E2%80%94-2020-02-14/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T21:52:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223754925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583901177\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002260033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dlrk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, dlrk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to just default this to on, instead of activating manually? Also, it would be awesome to have the brakes automatically activate on touchdown\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wouldn\u0027t hold your breath on that one (not the author obviously, but I do have some insight on this).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s incredibly difficult to accurately detect a touchdown. If a plane bounces \u003Cem\u003Eeven slightly\u003C/em\u003E while taking off then the situation will quickly change from Flying, to Landed, and back to Flying. A touchdown mod would almost certainly be looking for a vessel going from Flying to Landed. There are ways around that of course, but it\u0027s not an easy thing to account for all the variables.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-11T21:53:37Z\u0022 title=\u002203/11/2020 09:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by severedsolo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dlrk","CreatedById":60033,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-14T16:35:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002280345\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/80345-severedsolo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@severedsolo\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m a bit confused about the effect of the interval. If it\u0027s shorter (i.e. 0.1s) does that lead to a safer landing or a longer one?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theonegalen","CreatedById":71012,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-05T23:53:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone having problems with this in 1.10.1? I\u0027m going to give it a shot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}